<appendix id="app_custom">
  <title>Custom SoC documentation</title>

  <section id="sec_soc_mmap">
    <title>'agathe'/'beatrix' specific maps</title>

    <section>
      <title>ZPUng address map</title>

      <para>The ZPUng has a no shared Program/Data/Heap and stack memory,
      instead, it uses a separate stack as shown in <xref
      linkend="tbl_addrmap_zpung"/>.</para>

      <table id="tbl_addrmap_zpung">
        <title>ZPUng v1 RAM default address map</title>

        <tgroup cols="2">
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry align="center">Address range</entry>

              <entry align="center">Description</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>

          <tbody>
            <row>
              <entry><constant>0x0000-0x3fff</constant></entry>

              <entry>Program memory and Heap</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry><hardware><constant>0x4000-0x41ff</constant></hardware></entry>

              <entry>Stack memory</entry>
            </row>

            <row>
              <entry><hardware><constant>0x8000-0xffff</constant></hardware></entry>

              <entry>Memory mapped registers (MMR)</entry>
            </row>
          </tbody>
        </tgroup>
      </table>

      <note>
        <para>The stack memory start address always immediately follows the
        program memory (which is configured by CONFIG_BRAM_ADDR_WIDTH)</para>
      </note>
    </section>
  </section>
</appendix>
